+<a id=opt-sampling></a>
+#### `sampling` (Object)
+
+Default: `undefined`
+
+Per-level sampling rules for reducing log volume in high-throughput scenarios.
+Keys are level labels (e.g. `info`, `debug`, custom level names) or `'*'` as a
+fallback for any level not explicitly configured. Each value is a rule object
+(or a shorthand — see below).
+
+When `sampling` is not configured, the logging hot path is completely
+unaffected — the generated log methods are byte-for-byte identical to a logger
+without the option. When a rule is configured for a level, the sampling
+decision is taken *before* message formatting and serialization, so dropped
+logs incur almost no cost.
+
+Rule properties (all optional, applied in the order listed):
+
+* `every` (Integer): emit only every Nth call (the 1st, N+1th, 2N+1th, ...).
+* `rate` (Number): probability between `0` and `1` that a call is emitted.
+* `limit` (Integer) / `window` (Number): emit at most `limit` calls per
+  `window` milliseconds (fixed window).
+* `test` (Function): custom predicate `(args, level) => boolean` receiving the
+  raw log-method arguments. Return `false` to drop. `this` is the logger.
+* `dedupe` (Object): suppress repeated identical messages.
+  * `dedupe.window` (Number): deduplication window in milliseconds. The first
+    occurrence of a given key is emitted immediately; duplicates within the
+    window are dropped. When the window expires a single summary line is
+    emitted at the same level with a
+    `sampling: { suppressed: <n>, key: <key> }` property.
+  * `dedupe.key` (Function): optional `(args) => key` extractor. By default the
+    message format string is used (or `Error#message` if the first argument is
+    an `Error`).
+
+Shorthands: a number value is treated as `{ rate: <n> }`, a function value is
+treated as `{ test: <fn> }`, and `false`/`null` disables sampling for that
+level (useful when overriding on a child).
+
+```js
+const logger = pino({
+  sampling: {
+    debug: { rate: 0.05 },               // ~5% of debug logs
+    info:  { every: 10 },                // every 10th info log
+    warn:  { limit: 100, window: 1000 }, // max 100 warn logs / second
+    error: { dedupe: { window: 5000 } }, // collapse identical error storms
+    '*':   { rate: 1 }                   // everything else passes through
+  }
+})
+```
+
+Child loggers inherit the parent's sampling rules (and share their counters)
+by default. A child may override or disable individual levels via
+[`options.sampling`](#options-sampling).
+
 <a id=opt-base></a>
 #### `base` (Object)
 
@@ -968,6 +1022,22 @@ child.info('message proxied!')
