 ```
 
+<a id="options-sampling"></a>
+##### `options.sampling` (Object | null | false)
+
+Per-level sampling rules for the child logger. Rules are shallow-merged over
+the parent's rules (so you can override a single level) and the child gets
+its own independent counters. Pass `null` or `false` to disable sampling on
+the child entirely, or set an individual level to `false` to opt that level
+out of an inherited rule.
+
+```js
+const parent = pino({ sampling: { info: { rate: 0.1 }, debug: { every: 100 } } })
+const child = parent.child({}, { sampling: { info: false } }) // info unsampled, debug inherited
+```
+
+* See [`sampling` logger option](#opt-sampling)
+
 ##### `options.redact` (Array | Object)
 
 Setting `options.redact` to an array or object will override the parent `redact` options. To remove `redact` options inherited from the parent logger set this value as an empty array (`[]`).
